🧠 FINAL MENTOR WISDOM
Rule 1: "Ripple Effect" Rule
Jitni HIGHER layer mein change karo → utna ZYADA impact
→ theme.liquid change = ENTIRE site affected
→ section change = ALL pages using that section affected
→ block change = ONLY that block's instances affected
→ snippet change = EVERYWHERE that snippet is rendered

Rule 2: "Shared Resource" Rule
SHARED files are POWERFUL but DANGEROUS:
→ product-card.liquid (6+ sections use it)
→ button.liquid (10+ sections use it)
→ image.liquid (15+ sections use it)
→ slideshow.js (2 sections share it)
→ _blocks.liquid (ALL sections depend on it)

ALWAYS: Search → Find all usages → Test all contexts → Then deploy

Rule 3: "Critical Path" Rule
Customer's purchase journey = CRITICAL PATH:
Home → Collection → Product → Cart → Checkout

FILES ON CRITICAL PATH (NEVER break these):
→ header.liquid (navigation)
→ main-collection.liquid (browsing)
→ product-information.liquid (product view)
→ variant-picker.js (selection)
→ product-form.js (add to cart)
→ main-cart.liquid (review)
→ component-cart-items.js (cart management)

Break ANY of these = LOST REVENUE

Rule 4: "Mobile First" Rule
60-70% traffic = mobile
EVERY section, block, snippet MUST work on mobile
Test order: Mobile → Tablet → Desktop (not other way!)

Rule 5: "Performance Budget" Rule
Each section should:
→ Load in < 200ms
→ Images < 200KB each (use Shopify CDN auto-resize)
→ JS < 50KB per section
→ Total page: < 3 seconds First Contentful Paint

HEAVY sections to watch:
→ slideshow (multiple large images)
→ product-information (gallery + multiple JS files)
→ main-collection (product grid + filters + pagination)


