File #48: predictive-search-styles.liquid
TYPE: CSS Generator Snippet
ROLE: Predictive search dropdown ka CSS inline generate karna
CALLED BY: snippets/search-modal.liquid (search modal ke andar)
CONNECTIONS: 1 file

WHY INLINE CSS (not external file)?
→ Search modal initially HIDDEN hai
→ External CSS file load karna = wasted bandwidth agar search use nahi hua
→ Inline CSS sirf TAB load hota hai jab search modal open ho
→ PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATION technique!

WHAT CSS IT GENERATES:
→ Dropdown width/height
→ Result item padding/margin
→ Hover states
→ Loading spinner styles
→ Responsive adjustments (mobile vs desktop width)
→ Animation (fade in/slide down)

LOGIC:
→ Reads theme settings (colors, fonts, border-radius)
→ Generates matching CSS dynamically
→ Output: <style> tag with search-specific styles

IF-THEN Logic:

IF: predictive-search-styles.liquid delete kiya
THEN: Search dropdown UNSTYLED — raw HTML dikhega
→ Ugly white box with misaligned text
→ Functional but TERRIBLE looking

IF: Theme colors change kiye settings mein
THEN: Yeh snippet automatically naye colors ka CSS generate karega
→ Search dropdown bhi match karega — NO manual update needed

IF: Mobile width adjust karna hai
THEN: Iss snippet mein media query change karo
→ Sirf search dropdown affected — baaki theme safe

