Format depends on merchant's inventory system:
→ Simple: "12345"
→ Structured: "CAT-SUBCAT-COLOR-SIZE" (WL-SHOE-BLU-42)
→ Barcode-based: "8901234567890"

HOW DYNAMIC UPDATE WORKS:
Product has 6 variants:
Variant 1 (Blue/S): SKU = "SHOE-BLU-S"
Variant 2 (Blue/M): SKU = "SHOE-BLU-M"
Variant 3 (Blue/L): SKU = "SHOE-BLU-L"
Variant 4 (Red/S): SKU = "SHOE-RED-S"
Variant 5 (Red/M): SKU = "SHOE-RED-M"
Variant 6 (Red/L): SKU = "SHOE-RED-L"

Customer selects "Red" + "M"
↓
variant-picker.js fires event: "variant changed"
↓
product-sku.js LISTENS to this event
↓
Updates display: SKU: SHOE-RED-M

WHO NEEDS SKU VISIBLE:
→ Wholesale buyers (they order by SKU)
→ Customer support (identify exact variant quickly)
→ Inventory management (warehouse teams)
→ B2B customers (purchase orders reference SKU)

WHO DOESN'T NEED IT:
→ Fashion/lifestyle brands (clutters design)
→ DTC brands (customers don't care about SKU)
→ Minimal designs (less is more)

IF-THEN Logic:

IF: sku.liquid block product page se remove kiya
THEN: SKU nahi dikhega — cosmetic only, no functional impact
→ Most B2C stores actually REMOVE this for cleaner look

IF: product-sku.js delete kiya
THEN: SKU STATIC reh jayega — variant change pe update nahi hoga
→ First variant ka SKU permanently dikhega
→ Wholesale buyer WRONG SKU copy karega → wrong order!

IF: Variant mein SKU field empty hai (admin mein nahi bhara)
THEN: "SKU: " label dikhega with blank value
→ UGLY — fix: hide block when SKU empty

IF: SKU block enable kiya + variant-picker nahi hai
THEN: SKU static dikhega (default variant ka)
→ Acceptable if single-variant product


