Merchant selects: "Show products from Summer Dresses collection"
↓
Product list section reads this selection
↓
Fetches products from that collection
↓
Renders product cards

SETTINGS:
→ Collection picker (search + select)
→ Products to show (4, 8, 12, 16)
→ Sort order (manual, best selling, price ascending, newest)

THIS IS A SETTINGS BLOCK — No visible output itself!
It doesn't render anything visible.
It just TELLS the parent section which products to fetch.

IF-THEN Logic:

IF: featured-collection block mein no collection selected
THEN: Product list section ko data nahi milega → "No products" message
→ OR: Shows ALL products (depending on fallback logic)

IF: Selected collection mein 2 products hain but "show 8" set hai
THEN: Sirf 2 products dikhenge — empty slots nahi dikhenge
→ Grid adjust hoga (2 items in grid that expects 8)

IF: Sort "best selling" set kiya
THEN: Collection ke products sales count se sort honge
→ Most popular products first → better conversion


