HOW AJAX FILTERING WORKS (facets.js):
Customer checks "Blue" color filter
↓
facets.js captures change event
↓
Constructs URL: /collections/summer?filter.v.option.color=Blue
↓
AJAX request to Shopify (section rendering API)
↓
Shopify returns ONLY filtered products HTML
↓
facets.js replaces product grid HTML (DOM morph)
↓
Page did NOT reload! Smooth experience!
↓
URL updates (browser history push) — bookmarkable!
Product count updates
Active filter badges appear

MOBILE BEHAVIOR:
Desktop: Filter sidebar LEFT of products
Mobile: Filter button → Modal/drawer opens → Apply → Close
(Screen too small for sidebar)

IF-THEN Logic:

IF: filters.liquid block remove kiya collection page se
THEN: NO FILTERS! Customer 500 products manually browse karega
→ Terrible UX for stores with 50+ products
→ Customer can't find what they want → LEAVES
→ Conversion rate -30% to -50% without filters!

IF: facets.js delete kiya
THEN: Filters still RENDER (HTML exists) but click pe:
→ Full page reload hoga (traditional form submit)
→ Much slower experience
→ Customer feels jarring refresh on every filter
→ STILL WORKS — just bad UX (progressive enhancement!)

IF: snippets/list-filter.liquid missing
THEN: Individual filter groups (Color, Size, Brand) nahi render honge
→ Filter sidebar blank/broken

IF: snippets/price-filter.liquid missing
THEN: Price slider nahi dikhega — price filter unavailable
→ Customer budget ke hisab se filter nahi kar sakta

IF: Product mein tags/options properly set nahi hain
THEN: Filters mein values nahi dikhenge
→ "Color" filter shows 0 options if products don't have color option
→ FIX: Products mein proper options set karo admin mein

IF: Collection mein 10,000 products hain + 50 color values
THEN: Filter lists very LONG → needs "Show More" button
→ assets/show-more.js handles this
→ Default: Show 10 values → "Show 20 more" button

IF: Customer 5 filters simultaneously lagaye
THEN: Products drastically reduce (intersection logic)
→ "Blue" AND "Size M" AND "Nike" AND "$50-$100" AND "In Stock"
→ Maybe 2-3 products match → show count in real-time
→ IF 0 match → "No products match your filters" message + Clear button


